Author: baur <baurzhansahariev@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Sep 24 13:49:44 2025 +0200

    bp: https://github.com/opensearch-project/OpenSearch/commit/f059738aaceec3ecd45c2962c87a2d83cc8cbe46
    
    Prevent serialisation failures (for example, because of a CircuitBreakerException) leading to node disconnects
    
    See also https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/issues/75334
    
    (cherry picked from commit ffeaa8be341dc98fcd4a30f3b6be8df9ae8b5dcf)

diff --git a/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.13.rst b/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.13.rst
index 2953b4da61..d85a61e9dc 100644
--- a/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.13.rst
+++ b/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.10.13.rst
@@ -51,3 +51,7 @@ Fixes
 - Fixed an issue that could lead to PostgreSQL wire protocol messages being sent
   in the wrong order to the client. The issue was triggered when using batched
   statements where one of the statements caused a parse or bind error.
+
+- Fixed an issue that could lead to stuck jobs, memory leaks and even make a
+  cluster unstable when a query with a ``LIMIT`` clause was interrupted by a
+  ``CircuitBreakingException``.
